From 8c815e898fe13f9ed436825a77399561597cd708 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Maksim Ivanov <emaxx@google.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Dec 2025 15:46:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Reland-2 "[sandbox] Cage for ExternalStrings when memory
 corruption API"

Fix the original CL's mjsunit test slowness by using std::unique_ptr
instead of std::vector for string resources - this makes the in-sandbox
OOB reads detected as fast as before, without committing and
initializing the backing storage for a potentially corrupted
arbitrarily big size.

Also increase the cage contents to 9 GB, to not prevent allocations
of maximum-sized strings.

Original change's description:
> [sandbox] Cage for ExternalStrings when memory corruption API
>
> When fuzzing/testing with memory_corruption_api enabled, move all
> external string resources into a separate cage with a large reserved
> guard zone at the end. In testing crash/failure handlers, ignore OOB
> reads within this cage.
>
> This allows us to skip such reports from being triaged for this known
> issue in the sandbox attacker model.

Bug: 329781444

